10:24.157 --> 10:30.964 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It is a recipe for cleaner --
dirtier air
and contaminated water.

10:30.997 --> 10:33.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's really a bad deal for the
American public.

10:33.199 --> 10:37.770 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The president
tweeted, Senator,
you probably know, that this is
a budget that

10:37.804 --> 10:39.806 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
puts America first.

10:39.839 --> 10:44.177 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's a budget that makes safety
the prime
consideration.

10:44.210 --> 10:45.845 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

10:45.879 --> 10:50.149 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
CHRIS VAN HOLLEN: Well,
actually, it makes
America last in terms of
investing in our

10:50.183 --> 10:54.354 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
people, investing in our
economy, investing
in our national infrastructure,
something

10:54.387 --> 11:00.126 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that candidate Trump talked a
whole lot about,
yet they cut the infrastructure
budget here

11:00.159 --> 11:02.262 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
by over 13 percent.

11:02.295 --> 11:10.069 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, a lot of what he talked
about on the campaign
trail is actually under attack
in this budget,

11:10.103 --> 11:15.174 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
including, I have to say,
important economic
development programs and
infrastructure programs

11:15.208 --> 11:17.977 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
for rural America.

11:18.011 --> 11:25.351 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He does dramatically increase
Pentagon spending,
but he cuts the funding for the
State Department.

11:25.385 --> 11:31.391 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the State Department funding
is designed
to help keep us out of wars and
to save lives

11:31.424 --> 11:33.026 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and money.

11:33.059 --> 11:36.429 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's what Secretary
Mattis, his own
defense secretary, has had to
say.

11:36.462 --> 11:38.798 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, this doesn't help America.

11:38.831 --> 11:42.835 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In fact, it really erodes
American influence
around the world.

11:42.869 --> 11:46.773 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, what
they're saying is
the Pentagon budget, the defense
spending

11:46.806 --> 11:52.879 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in this country has been cut
back so much
that the United States is
vulnerable, and

11:52.912 --> 11:58.451 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that this is a critical moment
for the United
States to restore the spending
for defense

11:58.484 --> 12:01.321 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that should have been there for
the last number
of years.

12:01.354 --> 12:03.156 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

12:03.189 --> 12:06.392 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
CHRIS VAN HOLLEN: Well,
actually, that's just
another alternative fact coming
out of this

12:06.426 --> 12:07.393 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
administration.

12:07.427 --> 12:09.195 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We have had robust defense
spending.

12:09.228 --> 12:15.768 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I can support additional
investment in our
national security, but we just
saw a few months

12:15.802 --> 12:22.108 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ago reports out of the Pentagon
about over
$120 billion in wasteful
spending.

12:22.141 --> 12:27.981 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In fact, Donald Trump has talked
about these
huge cost overruns on Pentagon
projects.

12:28.014 --> 12:34.721 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So we'd be much better off
managing those
resources better, than simply
writing a new

12:34.754 --> 12:38.725 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
check to the Pentagon, which, by
the way,
is the one federal government
agency that

12:38.758 --> 12:41.494 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
has not been able to pass an
audit.

12:41.527 --> 12:44.564 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, look, I'm all for investing
on our national
security.

12:44.597 --> 12:50.336 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have to do it, but we also
have to recognize
our national strength includes
making sure

12:50.370 --> 12:52.238 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
our kids get a good education.

12:52.271 --> 12:56.542 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he cut the Department of
Education by
close to 15 percent.

12:56.576 --> 12:59.579 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It includes making sure we have
a healthy
population.

12:59.612 --> 13:06.252 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he dramatically cut funding
for medical
research to help develop cures
and treatments.

13:06.285 --> 13:11.457 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, this is really something
that's going
to hurt most of the country.

13:11.491 --> 13:17.130 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You know, the folks at the very
top who just
got a big tax cut as part of the
Trumpcare

13:17.163 --> 13:20.199 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
plan aren't going to be hurt,
but everybody
else is.

13:20.233 --> 13:23.870 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Senator, again,
I'm sure you
know, but what the -- I just
heard the budget

13:23.903 --> 13:25.505 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
director making this argument
today.

13:25.538 --> 13:29.242 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He was pressed on some of these
cuts, for
example, in education.

13:29.275 --> 13:34.547 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He said the administration has
looked very
closely at so many of these
domestic spending

13:34.580 --> 13:39.585 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
programs, and he says where
there is no evidence
that people are actually being
helped, these

13:39.619 --> 13:41.054 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
programs cannot continue.

13:41.087 --> 13:42.822 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

13:42.855 --> 13:45.792 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHRIS VAN HOLLEN: Well, we
certainly shouldn't
be asking taxpayers to invest in
programs

13:45.825 --> 13:47.994 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
that don't help.

13:48.027 --> 13:54.867 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the reality is that the
after-school programs
to try to make sure that kids
are in a productive

13:54.901 --> 13:59.706 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
environment after school hours
and not out
on the streets, that actually is
an important

13:59.739 --> 14:00.707 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
program.

14:00.740 --> 14:02.842 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's been underfunded in the
United States.

14:02.875 --> 14:08.114 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are other career and
training programs
that have shown good results,
and they're

14:08.147 --> 14:09.515 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
cutting them.

14:09.549 --> 14:12.819 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The same is true with respect to
some of our
manufacturing programs.

14:12.852 --> 14:18.725 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, here's a president who
says he wants
to restore American
manufacturing, and yet

14:18.758 --> 14:25.031 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
he cuts the manufacturing
extension program,
which helps take innovations and
make sure

14:25.064 --> 14:28.735 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that they're available to
industry throughout
the United States.

14:28.768 --> 14:31.237 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, this is a very short-sighted
budget.

14:31.270 --> 14:36.909 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I have to say that Donald Trump
said he was
going to be there for the
forgotten people.

14:36.943 --> 14:39.278 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In this budget, he forgets those
people.

14:39.312 --> 14:41.047 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I mean, they're not even an
afterthought.

14:41.080 --> 14:44.417 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Senator Chris Van
Hollen, a
member of the Senate Budget
Committee, we

14:44.450 --> 14:45.418 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
thank you, sir.

14:45.451 --> 14:46.419 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

14:46.452 --> 14:48.154 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
CHRIS VAN HOLLEN: Thank you.

14:48.187 --> 14:51.924 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And for an
opposing view, we
turn now to Representative Todd
Rokita.

14:51.958 --> 14:57.029 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's a Republican from Indiana
and he is vice
chairman of the House Budget
Committee.

14:57.063 --> 14:59.799 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Congressman Rokita, welcome to
the "NewsHour."

14:59.832 --> 15:05.304 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think you just heard at least
part of what
Senator Van Hollen said, and
that is, in this

15:05.338 --> 15:11.177 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
budget proposal, the president
is forgetting
some of the very people he said
he wanted

15:11.210 --> 15:12.178 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to be elected to help.

15:12.211 --> 15:13.179 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

15:13.212 --> 15:14.580 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
TODD ROKITA (R), Indiana: Yes, I
heard that.

15:14.614 --> 15:16.916 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And Chris is a friend from the
House Budget
Committee.

15:16.949 --> 15:21.320 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He was ranking member when I was
vice chairman
there last Congress.

15:21.354 --> 15:23.456 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And, you know, I heard some of
the same rhetoric.

15:23.489 --> 15:26.592 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He's a good man, but let me just
say this.

15:26.626 --> 15:30.997 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president, with the budget
that he put
forward today, recognizing that
it's his request,

15:31.030 --> 15:35.501 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it's not the budget -- we still
have our Article
I powers under the Constitution,
and we will

15:35.535 --> 15:43.376 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
use them, as congress men and
women, to reconcile
different priorities and make
sure that we're

15:43.409 --> 15:45.378 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
continue to march forward for
the American
people.

15:45.411 --> 15:51.551 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But I would say that the
forgotten man that
President Trump campaigned for
should be proud

15:51.584 --> 15:53.352 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of what was done in the budget.

15:53.386 --> 15:58.558 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
First of all, the one thing,
Judy, that the
federal government does
constitutionally and

15:58.591 --> 16:01.494 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
does well is our national
defense.

16:01.527 --> 16:06.599 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I will quibble with Mr. Van
Hollen if
he says that our national
defense has been

16:06.632 --> 16:08.501 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
taken care of.

16:08.534 --> 16:13.539 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It only makes up about 20
percent of our budget
historically, but it took 50
percent of the

16:13.573 --> 16:14.874 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
sequester cuts.

16:14.907 --> 16:16.242 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So, fair is fair.

16:16.275 --> 16:19.745 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we're getting back to
rebalancing that.

16:19.779 --> 16:24.851 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Otherwise, Judy, this is a
traditional -- as
you would see in a economic
textbook of some

16:24.884 --> 16:28.120 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
kind, traditional guns vs.
butter argument.

16:28.154 --> 16:32.692 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And for eight years or so, we
have been doling
out a lot of butter, a lot of
domestic programs.

16:32.725 --> 16:37.797 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And what Mr. Trump is suggesting
here is that
we rebalance and put a little
bit more into

16:37.830 --> 16:42.802 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
our guns to make sure that we're
protected
from a military standpoint, that
we're safe,

16:42.835 --> 16:44.303 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
and...

16:44.337 --> 16:46.906 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, let me just
interrupt
you there, if you don't mind.

16:46.939 --> 16:47.907 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

16:47.940 --> 16:49.075 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
TODD ROKITA: Yes.

16:49.108 --> 16:50.910 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Because I want to
ask you about
that.

16:50.943 --> 16:53.946 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We did hear Senator Van Hollen
say, yes, it's
good to spend more on defense,
but he said

16:53.980 --> 16:57.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
there are problems with defense
spending,
that it hasn't -- he said we
haven't even

16:57.850 --> 16:59.518 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
seen a serious audit.

16:59.552 --> 17:04.223 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I do want to ask you about
some of the
domestic cuts, education down 15
percent,

17:04.257 --> 17:11.430 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
medical research, major cut, a
20-some percent
cut in the environment, 21
percent.

17:11.464 --> 17:13.900 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
How -- what are these cuts?

17:13.933 --> 17:14.901 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What is going to be cut?

17:14.934 --> 17:16.836 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

17:16.869 --> 17:19.071 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TODD ROKITA: Well, I have been
in a budget
hearing all day repealing and
replacing Obamacare.

17:19.105 --> 17:22.875 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, you know, I don't have all
the details,
and I didn't write the document.

17:22.909 --> 17:25.511 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Like I said, we are going to
digest that all
in the Budget Committee.

17:25.544 --> 17:30.783 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But let me just, from an
overview perspective,
say that what I'm seeing so far
is that what

17:30.816 --> 17:36.088 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is being -- quote, unquote --
"cut" are really
duplicative programs and
programs that shouldn't

17:36.122 --> 17:37.857 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
be in the agencies that they're
in.

17:37.890 --> 17:44.597 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we see this throughout
government, 10,
20, 30 programs that pretend to
do the same

17:44.630 --> 17:47.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
thing, but don't do it well.

17:47.166 --> 17:52.538 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so that's what I see Mr.
Trump and Mick
Mulvaney, the OMB director,
doing here, is

17:52.571 --> 17:54.507 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
really streamlining government.

17:54.540 --> 17:56.442 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he's also making good on
other campaign
promises.

17:56.475 --> 18:00.513 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm the kindergarten through
12th grade education
chairman in the House,
subcommittee education

18:00.546 --> 18:02.448 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
chairman.

18:02.481 --> 18:09.588 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And what we're seeing here is
Mr. Trump making
good on school choice, the idea
that the property

18:09.622 --> 18:13.559 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of parents, the tax dollars, are
actually
following the child more to a
school that

18:13.592 --> 18:17.396 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
fits them, not being shackled to
a school
that doesn't work for them.

18:17.430 --> 18:18.731 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And that's an important point.

18:18.764 --> 18:19.765 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And that's not new money.

18:19.799 --> 18:21.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That's reprogrammed money.

18:21.267 --> 18:23.569 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So, it's money being
reprioritized.

18:23.602 --> 18:26.272 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's exactly, Judy, what a
budget is
about, and that's what he's
doing.

18:26.305 --> 18:30.977 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So the cuts in
medical research,
for example -- and I didn't
mention cuts in

18:31.010 --> 18:32.511 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
agriculture.

18:32.545 --> 18:37.850 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We heard Senator Van Hollen
speak about extension
programs in agriculture.

18:37.883 --> 18:40.853 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You're comfortable with all the
cuts the administration
is proposing?

18:40.886 --> 18:42.288 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

18:42.321 --> 18:44.023 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TODD ROKITA: Well, like I say, I
haven't looked
at the whole document.

18:44.056 --> 18:48.461 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I have been in an
eight-or-so-hour markup
on repealing and replacing
Obamacare, but

18:48.494 --> 18:50.262 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
we will look at all that.

18:50.296 --> 18:54.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And what I'm saying that I'm
comfortable with
is getting rid of the
duplication, getting

18:54.433 --> 18:58.771 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
rid of programs that are outside
the agency's
jurisdiction.

18:58.804 --> 19:00.573 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm for streamlining.

19:00.606 --> 19:03.609 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm for the president keeping
good on his
promises to the forgotten man
and all the

19:03.642 --> 19:04.744 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
rest of us.

19:04.777 --> 19:06.479 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that's what I'm seeing in
the budget so
far.

19:06.512 --> 19:10.449 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then, again, also, Judy, I
will say that
we will go through the budget
process.

19:10.483 --> 19:14.220 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The budget -- the president's
budget is just
a budget request.

19:14.253 --> 19:16.022 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The real budget is going to come
through the
House Budget Committee.

19:16.055 --> 19:17.356 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's going to come through
Chris' committee.

19:17.390 --> 19:20.926 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it doesn't even have to be
signed by the
president.

19:20.960 --> 19:23.963 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It goes into effect without his
signature.

19:23.996 --> 19:25.765 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, that's our Article I powers.

19:25.798 --> 19:29.235 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And you can be assured that
we're going to
look at every item, because
that's our job

19:29.268 --> 19:30.870 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and we will do it no matter who
the president
is.

19:30.903 --> 19:34.073 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And that's a
reminder of the
way the process really works.

19:34.106 --> 19:35.875 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

